                  <idno type="invno">P.Tebt.0124</idno>
               </msIdentifier>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>Petition of a group of cleruchs of the Arsinoite nome, who apparently wish to be let off some payment. Following the petition are a group of decrees, dealing with disputed ownership and amnesty for certain offenses, change in holders and successors, freeing of newly promoted katoikoi from previous burdens, and remission of taxation. These apparently are philanthropa, documents offered in support of the petitioners' claim.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Recto: published</note>
                     <note type="general">Margins: top, 1.5 cm.; bottom, 3.8 cm.</note>
                     <note type="general">Menches archive</note>
                     <note type="general">Frame 3/6 = Col. I; Frame 4/6 = Col. II.</note>
                     <note type="lines">2 cols. (45 lines) on verso across the fibers.</note>
                     <note type="paleography">Small regular cursive.</note>
                     <note type="recto_verso">Also on verso: unidentified texts. On Recto: List of holders of temple and cleruchic lands (P.Tebt.1108).</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <p>7 papyri ; 28.5 x 24 cm. or smaller.</p>
               </physDesc>
